        <abstract>
            <p>Ogle will keep JT’s suggestion in mind in observing less hairy races of man and the lower animals.</p>
            <p>Asks JT whether he can help Ogle on a troublesome point on the colour of tissues with olfactory nerves, and the relation of colour to the absorption of odours. Does JT’s respirator deprive odorous substances of their smell?</p>
        </abstract>
